{
  "texts": [
    "The probability of addition and deletion of edges is also uniformly distributed, and it is based on the prior that the semantics of the graph are robust to the connection of edges.",
    "Edge feature masking is similar to attribute masking, which improves the robustness of the model to weight changes or different types of edges by randomly masking the features of the edges.",
    "Subgraph-level augmentation mainly employs subgraph sampling techniques, where subgraphs are extracted from the graph by random walks.",
    "Subgraph sampling is based on the a priori that the semantics of the graph can be well preserved in the local subgraph structure, which enhances the generalization of the model across different datasets (You et al. 2020).",
    "Overall, with these data augmentation methods, graph datasets can be effectively extended to improve the performance and robustness of graph neural networks in the face of insufficient data, non-uniform distribution, or structural changes."
  ]
}